8   Working with Numbers
    He talks about:
	    round()    which rounds to the nearest integer
		abs()      which gets the absolute value
	Python has few built in math functions.  If you need more you need to get the math 'module'. To do this enter 'import math' the beginning of your code.
	'math' is an object so we use 'math.a_math_method' to access it's methods.
	math.ceil() rounds.
	To get the list of math module methods google 'python 3 math module',. It will take you to 'docs.python.org/3/library/math'

