Control_Flow
1   Comparison Operator
    "bag" > 'apple' because srings are in alphabetical order.
	'bag' != 'BAG' because ord('b') = 98 but ord('B') = 66. Note:the ascii value of 'A' is 97.

*******************************************************************************
2   Conditional Statements
    Make a decision with an if statement.
	if 'conditional :    //this conditionalis any expression that results in a boolean value
	   /* code to execute*/
	   // the python interpreter executes all the indented code after the if statement.
	Elif follows 'if'. If the if conditional was false but the elif is true the elif code executes.
	Else folllows all the ifs and elifs. If all there conditionals evaluated to false, the code in the else block executes.

*******************************************************************************
3   Ternary Operator
    The ternary operator is a more concise version of the if-ele statement.
	It's format is: code_to_execute_if_the_conditional_is_true if the_conditional else code_to_execute_if_the_conditinal_is_false
	You cannot put the ternary operator in the return statement in python. Set the ternary operator equal to a variable and return the var.

*******************************************************************************
4   Logical Operator
    The python logical operators are and, or and not.
	With the and operator if both booleans are true the conditional will return true.
	With the 'or' operator if at least one is true the conditional willl return true.
	The 'not' operator will return the opposite of the given boolean.
	You can group booleans and operators in parentheses
	
*******************************************************************************
5   Short circuit evaluation
    If a conditional has the and operator the conditional will return false when it reaches the first false because
    	there is now way the conditional can return true no matter what happens after that point.
	If a conditional has the 'or' opertor the conditional willl return true after is sees the first true boolean because
	    it doesn't matter what happens after. There is at least one true.

*******************************************************************************
6   Chaining comparison operators
    You can write 'if age >= 18 and age < 65:' as 'if 18 <= age < 65:

