    He explained how the code executes and the indecies change with nested loops.

*******************************************************************************
11  Iterables
    The range function returns an object of type range.
	Range is an iterable objrct so we can use it in a for loop.
	Other iterable objects are strings and lists.

*******************************************************************************
12  While Loops
    Use a while loop to repeat some code as long as some condition is true.
	A python shell is a while loop that keeps running until you enter ctrl+d.

*******************************************************************************
13  Infinite Loops
    Mosh says you can intentinally create an infinite loop and use some other way of breaking out of it.
	He suggests a conditional and a break statement.
	
